  "TSH": {
    "category": "Endocrinology - Thyroid Hormones",
    "english_name": "Thyroid Stimulating Hormone",
    "explanation": "Thyroid function is assessed through TSH (Thyroid Stimulating Hormone), T4 (Thyroxine), and T3 (Triiodothyronine). TSH is produced by the pituitary gland and stimulates the thyroid to produce T4 and T3. T4 and T3 are the active forms of thyroid hormones that regulate metabolism, energy production, and body temperature. Together, these measurements provide a comprehensive view of thyroid function. Elevated TSH with low T4/T3 suggests hypothyroidism, while low TSH with high T4/T3 indicates hyperthyroidism.",
    "unit": "mU/L"
  },
